From David Vanderbyl Subject Re A question about outlet Aart Olsen writes I noticed at the fusebox that some circuits have the with ground and that on these circuits the ground wire was tied to the same bus as the neutral white This is contrary to the electrical code and should be Sorry but this is exactly according to the No need to be sorry I blew it on this At the main breaker box where there is a thick wire ground leading to the earth both neutral and ground are hooked to this In any other breaker box or an outlet box the ground and neutral must not be connected